bug.short_desc: [abrt] spacefm: gdk_x11_drag_context_drag_status(): spacefm killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Trying to drag&drop a file, whichever one of the four possible options in Preferences is chosen, SpaceFM aborts.
This happens with wayland, X11 and gnome-classic.
Version-Release number of selected component: spacefm-1.0.5-3.101.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: spacefm crash_function: gdk_x11_drag_context_drag_status executable: /usr/bin/spacefm global_pid: 1921 kernel: 4.10.8-200.fc25.x86_64 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (2 frames) #0 gdk_x11_drag_context_drag_status at gdkdnd-x11.c:2442 #1 on_dir_tree_view_drag_motion at ptk/ptk-dir-tree-view.c:876

Looks like drag & dropping file works for me.
Would you tell me some detailed procedure or create a movie when the crash happens?
